Title: Filtering and parameter estimation in a simple linear system driven by a fractional Brownian motion  
Author: Alain Le Breton 
Keyword: Key Words and Phrases: Fractional Brownian motion; Optimal filter; Best linear unbiased estimator; Maximum likelihood estimator.  
Note: AMS 1991 Subject Classification: Primary 60G35, 62M20; Secondary 60G15, 93E11.  
Address: B.P. 53 38041 Grenoble Cedex 09, France  
Affiliation: LMC/IMAG, Universite J. Fourier,  
Abstract: The problem of optimal filtering is investigated in a continuous time linear Gaussian system where the signal is a fixed random variable and the noise driving the observation process is a fractional Brownian motion with Hurst parameter H 2 (1=2; 1). Closed form expressions are derived both for the optimal filter and the variance of the filtering error. Then an application to the determination of the best linear unbiased estimator in a related parameter estimation problem is discussed. Finally integral transformations which change a fractional Brownian motion to martingales are identified and an elementary approach to a Girsanov type formula is developed which shows that the estimator is in fact the maximum likelihood estimator. 
